make registercontroller



//JWT workflow


1.first install jsonwebtoken
2. generate token in utils/generateToken.js using JsonWebTokenError.sign(id, secret, exprire)
3. after user save in controller sendToken(user, res, 201)

so workflow from usercontroller call sendToken(user,res,201) -> sendToken() call generateToken(user.id)-> generateToken() make token using JsonWebTokenError.sign(id, secretkey, expiresIn) 
->back to generateToken() and get the token then i make a cookie with token res.cookei("token", token) (like key is added in an envelop)


4. now make login register and sendToken(user, res, 201) then like before steps it generate store in cookie and logged in
5. now make Middleware/authMiddleware.js in which isLogin checks identity proof as taken token from res.cookies.token then decode by JsonWebTokenError.verify(token, secretkey) then store in req.user and next

6. now add bcrypt make salt and hash then in loginuser bcrypt.compare